parameters.text:
=You will receive lead details, a research prompt, and optionally personalization notes.

Task:
1) Use the web search tool to research the person and their company.
2) Draft a short, highly personalized outreach email.
3) If personalization_notes are provided, USE THEM to make the email more personal.
4) Return STRICT JSON exactly matching the schema below.

Input lead details:
Name: {{ $json.output.full_name || $('Format Data Script').item.json.full_name }}
Email: {{ $json.output.email || $('Format Data Script').item.json.email_norm }}
Phone: {{ $json.output.phone || $('Format Data Script').item.json.phone_norm }}
Inquiry Type: {{ $('Format Data Script').item.json["Inquiry Type"] }}
Comments: {{ $('Format Data Script').item.json["Comments"] }}

Customer Status: {{ $json.output.customer_status }}

Research prompt from upstream agent:
{{ $json.output.perplexity_prompt }}

Personalization Notes (if existing customer):
{{ JSON.stringify($json.output.personalization_notes || {}) }}

Output JSON schema (must match exactly):
{
  "email": {
    "to": "",
    "subject": "",
    "body_html": ""
  },
  "research_summary": ["..."],
  "sources": ["..."]
}

Rules:
- If personalization notes include personal details (hobbies, family), reference them naturally.
- If they're an existing customer, acknowledge the prior relationship.
- Only include facts you found online or from personalization notes. Do not invent details.
- Keep the email 120–180 words, professional, with a clear CTA.
- research_summary MUST be an array of strings.
- sources MUST be an array of source URLs as strings.

Output rules:
Return ONLY valid JSON that matches the schema exactly.
The first character must be { and the last character must be }.
Do not include markdown, code fences, commentary, or extra keys.

parameters.jsonSchemaExample:
{
  "email": {
    "to": "john@example.com",
    "subject": "Quick question about your data needs",
    "body_html": "<p>Hi John,</p><p>...</p>"
  },
  "research_summary": ["Finding 1", "Finding 2"],
  "sources": ["https://example.com/source1", "https://example.com/source2"]
}

